<br>
It is designed to give enchanters something to do on ubermob encounters (nuke), so the only places people have reported it dropping were things like tormax and ubermob dragons.<br>
<br>
Wanna chime in on some of those spells that Ol had mentioned....  I have every spell pre SoL except dementing visions, which i would like to have someday....<br>
<br>
Bedlam  = GREAT.  350 points of damage absorb you can cast componentless, WITHOUT any sort of healer agro from casting a rune.  Once you get this, you wont ever need to cast rune 3 again ( which absorbs less and has a component + agro associated with it ).<br>
<br>
Umbra = Toy.. only useful for soloing or when you do small groups without a cleric or shaman.  Same AC as shadow even.<br>
<br>
Torment of Argli = GREAT for the enchanter who does things like Temple of Veeshan.  This dot will allow a single enchanter to stop Gating / Complete healing on any mob it will land on.   The damage is negligable, but thats not the point.  If you can land this dot early on, and mana sieve a couple times... NOTHING will gate / Complete heal.  timing is sorta critical, but yes this is a spell you should concentrate on getting.<br>
<br>
Asphixiate = Kinda toy ( and pretty common spell too ).  Only useful if you are duo ing with a druid partner or something and want to add some damage by stacking dots.  Torment and Asphixiate stack, but take HELLA long to do damage.<br>
<br>
Group c2 is a lifesaver.. especially with the new /targetgroupbuff command.  This will let a single enchanter cast 4 times to buff an entire raid of 4 groups with c2, instead of about 20 times.  IMHO.. this spell is as important as Clarity 2 at level 54, and should be something you scribe when you ding.<br>
<br>
Gift of Brilliance = shrug.. I cast it.. Its nice cause i dont have to cast often, but the actual difference in gameplay is minimal if you dont have this one.. Dont kill yourself trying to get it.<br>
<br>
